{\par \b Syntax:}\par SCHUR(matrix)\par
{\par \b Description:}\par Schur Decomposition. Factors a square matrix into two matrices. If matrix is real, then the result is \{[[orthogonal]],[[upper-quasi triangular]]\}.\par If Complex mode is on and the matrix is complex, then the result is \par \{[[unitary]],[[upper-triangular]]\}.\par
{\par \b Example:}\par SCHUR([[1,2],[3,4]])\par }